The "Magnificent Seven," the group of stocks comprising Nvidia (NVDA), Alphabet (GOOG, GOOGL), Tesla (TSLA), Microsoft (MSFT), Amazon (AMZN), Meta (META), and Apple (AAPL), fueled market gains in 2023 and 2024.

recent_articles.title: Stock market today: Dow jumps, Nasdaq slides as Trump tax bill sails through Senate
Trump vs. Musk 2.0: Reignited feud sends Tesla stock lower
recent_articles.summary:
Tesla (TSLA) stock slides as CEO Elon Musk and President Trump are yet again arguing over social media.

Musk criticized Trump's big, beautiful bill, which moves to the House after narrowly passing through the Senate, saying the mega bill, which is expected to add trillions to the national debt, is "insane."

The president responded by threatening to cut US government subsidies to Musk's businesses, including Tesla and SpaceX (SPAX.PVT). Trump added that the richest man in the world would then have to "close up shop and head back home to South Africa."

Yahoo Finance's Head of News, Myles Udland, and Prairie Operating Co. executive vice president of market strategy and TheBigSkinny.com founder, Lou Basenese, sit down with Josh Lipton on Market Domination to discuss the latest.
